<p>I have defined this class aspect that is working fine for the services (don't allow access unless the user has the role MANAGER, but there is no restricton for the controller (?)</p>  <pre><code>@Aspect public class DeviceAspect extends ServiceSupport {       @Pointcut("execution(* fr.telecom.services.client.ManageLicenseService.*(..))")     public void manage() {     }      @Pointcut("execution(* fr.telecom.services.client.AwardService.*(..))")     public void award() {     }      @Pointcut("execution(* fr.telecom.services.client.DeviceService.*(..))")     public void handleDeviceServiceMethod() {     }      @Pointcut("execution(* fr.telecom.controller.manage.ImportController.*(..))")     public void handleImportController() {     }       @Before("fr.telecom.services.aop.DeviceAspect.handleImportController() || fr.telecom.services.aop.DeviceAspect.handleDeviceServiceMethod() || fr.telecom.services.aop.DeviceAspect.manage() || fr.telecom.services.aop.DeviceAspect.award()")     public void before(JoinPoint _jp) {         User user = getEcasUser();         if(user == null || user.getUserRole() != UserRole.MANAGER) {             throw new NoSufficientRoleException(user == null ? null : user.getUserRole(), UserRole.MANAGER);         }     }  } </code></pre>